From: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 21:30:00 +0800
Subject: Increase default SymLinks_DangerousLevel to 10

Change the default symbolic link dangerous level from 5 to 10.
This relaxes the symlink security checks while keeping the
IsSafePath() core defense active.

Level 10 (vs 5) changes:
- Disables the low-level check (level <= 5 && LowLevel < 0)
  that incorrectly rejects symlinks with ../ that don't actually
  escape the extraction root (e.g. winsxs/../../system32/*.dll).
- Disables the final-level check (level <= 5 && FinalLevel < 1).
- Disables the chain symlink filesystem check (CheckLinkPath_in_FS)
  to avoid false positives when intermediate directories are
  themselves symlinks (common in Wine prefixes).
- Disables hardlink-to-symlink rejection.

All real directory traversal attacks are still caught by the
IsSafePath() check on the constructed full path
(prefix path + link target).

Signed-off-by: lichenggang <lichenggang@uniontech.com>
---
 CPP/7zip/UI/Common/ArchiveExtractCallback.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

Index: 7zip/CPP/7zip/UI/Common/ArchiveExtractCallback.h
===================================================================
--- 7zip.orig/CPP/7zip/UI/Common/ArchiveExtractCallback.h
+++ 7zip/CPP/7zip/UI/Common/ArchiveExtractCallback.h
@@ -75,7 +75,7 @@ struct CExtractNtOptions
       ExtractOwner(false),
       PreserveATime(false),
       OpenShareForWrite(false),
-      SymLinks_DangerousLevel(5),
+      SymLinks_DangerousLevel(10),
       MemLimit((UInt64)(Int64)-1)
   {
     SymLinks.Val = true;
